# Fruvia Backend API Tests

### Register User Test 1 - Success
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "0123456789",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "displayName": "John Doe",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe"
}

###

### Register User Test 2 - Another User
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "0987654321",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "password": "securepass456",
  "displayName": "Jane Smith",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith"
}

###

### Register User Test 3 - Minimal Info
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "0111222333",
  "email": "minimal@example.com",
  "password": "pass123",
  "displayName": "Minimal User"
}

###

### Get User By ID (replace {userId} with actual ID from registration response)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users/{userId}

###

### Get Current User (requires authentication)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users/me

###

### Login Test
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Introspect Token (replace {token} with actual token from login)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/introspect
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "{token}"
}

###

### Logout Test
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "{token}"
}
